The Presidency has described a report claiming that Zahra, daughter of President Muhammadu Buhari, got fraudulently employed, as a lie. According to the online medium, Ms. Zahra Buhari-Indimi allegedly got employed as by the Petroleum Products Pricing Regulatory Agency (PPPRA) as a top executive, outside statutory procedures. However, Femi Adesina, the Special Adviser on Media and Publicity to President Muhammadu Buhari in a statement described the report as untrue, malicious and an attack on the president’s family image. [UPDATE] Boko Haram attack: Buhari in Maiduguri on sympathy… UPDATE: Nigeria gets three centres to test for coronavirus BREAKING: Buhari on sympathy visit to Maiduguri Robust Nigeria-Ethiopia cooperation will provide strong… ALSO READ: Insecurity: Visit other state to gauge feelings, PDP tells Buhari “Zahra, just like any other Nigerian, can work wherever she secures employment, we hasten to add that the story is false in every material particular. “The publication is untrue, malicious and meant to cast aspersions at first family since the tendentious platform claims the job was secured fraudulent, the statement reads. He, therefore, enjoined Nigerians to ignore the piece masquerading as a news story.   SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.